						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment of a slab lying near the well called <hi rend="italic">Nāgati-Avvara-bhāvi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kannara.</p>						

						<p>After recounting the royal <hi rend="italic">praśasti,</hi> the king is said to have been ruling from Kandhārapura. A <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> whose name is lost is introduced as governing from his headquarters at Lōkāpura. The inscription is very much damaged and almost all the details are worn out.</p>						

						</summary>
